HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 199
By Farmer
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Lindsay Whitted on
her selection as the 2024-2025 Sevier County
School System Grades PreK-4 Teacher of the
Year.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
specially recognize those outstanding teachers who have devoted their careers to providing the
highest-quality education for Tennessee's students; and
WHEREAS, Lindsay Whitted is one such estimable educator, who has distinguished
herself as a professional of the greatest dedication, ability, and integrity; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Whitted has been selected as the 2024-2025 Sevier County School
System Grades PreK-4 Teacher of the Year, a most befitting honor that recognizes the positive
influence she has on so many young lives; and
WHEREAS, a third-grade teacher at Seymour Primary School, Lindsay Whitted has
taught for ten years; she is an extremely talented and compassionate educator who works
assiduously to motivate her students to reach their full potential, both as scholars and as
citizens; and
WHEREAS, implementing cutting-edge educational techniques and data-driven
resources in her classroom, Ms. Whitted is dedicated to finding new and innovative ways to
ensure an enriching learning environment for her students; and
WHEREAS, a model servant leader, Ms. Whitted is always willing to sacrifice her
personal time to give extra assistance to a struggling student or to attend her students' athletic
undertakings; she has dedicated herself to addressing the whole personhood of her students,
rather than attempting to isolate their academic value; and
